Package: ubuntu-game-session
Version: 0.6
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>
Installed-Size: 17
Depends: gamescope, sxhkd, gdm3, snapd
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Description: Ubuntu Game Session (Steam OS-like gaming experience)
 Installs a Gamescope-based Steam Gamepad UI as an optional Wayland session.
 Users can select "Ubuntu Game Session" from the GDM login screen to launch
 the full-screen Steam interface — a Steam OS-like experience on Ubuntu.
 .
 Suitable for desktops and laptops as an optional manually-selected session.
 Install ubuntu-game-handheld for the full handheld console-mode experience
 with automatic boot into gaming mode.
